on_metro               =1953801\n|population_density_metro_km2   = auto\n|population_urban               =1953801\n|population_density_urban_km2   = auto\n|population_blank1_title        =\n|population_blank1              =\n|population_density_blank1_km2 =   \n<!-- General information  --------------->\n|timezone               = [[China Standard Time|China Standard]]\n|utc_offset             =  +8\n|coor_pinpoint = Putian Government Plaza\n|coordinates            = {{coord|25.4526|N|119.0078|E|type:adm2nd_region:CN-35_source:Gaode|format=dms|display=it}}\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       = [[Postal code of China|Postal code]]\n|postal_code            = 351100\n|area_code              = 0594\n|iso_code = [[ISO 3166-2:CN|CN-FJ-03]]\n|blank_name             = [[Gross domestic product|GDP]]\n|blank_info             = 2015<ref name=\"stat\" />\n|blank1_name            = &nbsp;- Total\n|blank1_info            = [[Renminbi|CNY]] 167.0 billion (US$25.70 billion)\n|blank2_name            = &nbsp;- per capita\n|blank2_info            = [[Renminbi|CNY]] 58,596 (US$9,014)\n|blank3_name            = &nbsp;- Growth\n|blank3_info            = {{increase}} 14.5%\n|blank4_name            = [[Licence plates of the People's Republic of China|License Plate Prefixes]]\n|blank4_info            = {{lang|zh-cn|\u95fdB}}\n|blank5_name            = [[varieties of Chinese|Local variety]]\n|blank5_info            = [[Puxian Min]]\n|blank6_name            =<!-- Major [[Nationalities of China|Nationalities]] -->\n|blank6_info            =\n|website                = {{url|www.putian.gov.cn}}\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n{{Infobox Chinese|c={{linktext|lang=zh|\u8386\u7530}}|psp=Putien|w=P'u<sup>2</sup>-t'ien<sup>2</sup>|p=P\u00fati\u00e1n<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://dict.revised.moe.edu.tw/cgi-bin/cbdic/gsweb.cgi?o=dcbdic&searchid=Z00000026377|script-title=zh:\u6559\u80b2\u90e8\u91cd\u7de8\u570b\u8a9e\u8fad\u5178\u4fee\u8a02\u672c|accessdate=17 August 2019|quote={{lang|zh-Hant|\u5b57\u8a5e \u3010\u8386\u7530\u7e23\u3011 \u6ce8\u97f3 \u3106\u3128\u02ca \u310a\u3127\u3122\u02ca \u3112\u3127\u3122\u02cb \u6f22\u8a9e\u62fc\u97f3}} {{lang|zh-Latn-pinyin|p\u00fa ti\u00e1n xi\u00e0n}}}}</ref>|h=Ph\u00fb-thi\u00e8n|poj=Ph\u00f4\u0358-chh\u00e2n|buc=Pu\u00f2-di\u00e8ng|hhbuc=P\u00f3-ch\u00e9ng}}\n\n'''Putian''' or '''Putien''' ({{zh|c={{linktext|\u8386\u7530}}}}) is a [[prefecture-level city]] in eastern [[Fujian]] province, China. It borders [[Fuzhou]] City to the north, [[Quanzhou]] City to the south, and the [[Taiwan Strait]]'s [[Xinghai Bay]] to the east.<ref>[http://www.fzu.edu.cn/fujian/eput.html Litchi City Putian<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110522183140/http://www.fzu.edu.cn/fujian/eput.html |date=2011-05-22 }}</ref> The [[Mulan River]] flows through the southern part of the city. It's built-up area made of 4 urban districts was home to 1,953,801 inhabitants as of 2010 census. The native language of the area is [[Pu-Xian Min]].\n\n==History==\n===Imperial era===\nPutian was first founded as an administrative area in the year of 568 as a county during the [[Liang Dynasty]].\n\nPutian was later re-established as a military administered city during the [[Song Dynasty]] with the stationing of military families and soldiers into the city during the period. [[Xinghua Prefecture]] was created in 979. It was abolished during the [[Yuan Dynasty]] in 1277.\n\nThe city greatly prospered during the [[Ming Dynasty]].\n\n===Contemporary era===\nOn August 21 and August 25, 1949, Putian and Xianyou County were captured by the [[People's Liberation Army]], respectively. The [[Wuqiu Island]]s were never successfully captured, and continue to be under [[Republic of China|ROC]] control. \nOn September 9, 1983, the State Council approved the establishment of Putian as a prefecture-level city. It has jurisdiction over Putian and Xianyou Counties, along with Chengxiang and Hanjiang Districts.\n\n==Administration==\nPutian's [[Prefecture-level city|municipal]] executive, legislature and [[Intermediate People's Court|judiciary]] are in [[Chengxiang District]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u57ce\u53a2\u533a}}), together with the [[Communist Party of China|CPC]] and [[Public Security Bureau|Public Security]] bureaux. The municipal region comprises three other [[District (PRC)|districts]] and one [[County (People's Republic of China)|county]]:\n\n*[[Hanjiang District, Putian|Hanjiang District]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u6db5\u6c5f\u533a}})\n*[[Licheng District, Putian|Licheng District]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u8354\u57ce\u533a}})\n*[[Xiuyu District]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u79c0\u5c7f\u533a}})\n*[[Xianyou County]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u4ed9\u6e38\u53bf}})\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!  Map\n|-\n| \n{{Image label begin|image=Administrative Division Putian prfc map.png|width={{{1|768}}}|link=}} \n{{Image label|x=870|y=810|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=[[Chengxiang District|'''Chengxiang''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1210|y=390|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=[[Hanjiang District, Putian|'''Hanjiang''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1220|y=870|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=[[Licheng District, Putian|'''Licheng''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1530|y=1190|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=[[Xiuyu District|'''Xiuyu''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=440|y=700|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=[[Xianyou County|'''Xianyou<br />County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=2000|y=1130|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=<span style=\"font-size:smaller;\">[[Xiaori Island]]</span>}}\n{{Image label|x=2050|y=1300|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=<span style=\"font-size:smaller;\">[[Nanri Island]]</span>}}\n{{Image label|x=1350|y=1600|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=<span style=\"font-size:smaller;\">[[Meizhou Island]]</span>}}\n{{Image label|x=1950|y=1500|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=<span style=\"font-size:smaller;\">[[Luci Island]]</span>}}\n{{Image label|x=2150|y=1700|scale={{{1|768}}}/2560|text=<span style=\"font-size:smaller;\">''[[Wuqiu, Kinmen|Wuqiu]]''<br />Note: Kinmen County, ROC (Taiwan)<br />is claimed by the PRC.</span>}}\n{{Image label end}}\n|}\n\n==Languages and ethnic groups==\nThe [[Han Chinese]] are the majority ethnic group.\n\n[[Puxian Min]] is the largest dialect spoken in Putian. It is a dialect of [[Min Chinese|Min]], a [[Chinese language]].\n\n==Economy==\nPutian has become an export base for Fujian products. The main industries are shoe-making, brewing, electronics, garments, fruits, vegetables, and machinery, electrical goods.<ref>[http://www.chinatoday.com.cn/English/e20033/putian.htm China today<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070907090651/http://www.chinatoday.com.cn/English/e20033/putian.htm |date=2007-09-07 }}</ref> In particular, the area is known for high-quality [[Counterfeit consumer goods|counterfeits]] of shoes<ref>{{cite news|last=Schmidle|first=Nicholas|title=Inside the Knockoff-Tennis-Shoe Factory|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/22/magazine/22fake-t.html|accessdate=8 September 2010|newspaper=New York Times|date=2010-08-19}}</ref> and the domination of [[Healthcare in China|Chinese private healthcare]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Putian phenomenon|url=http://www.gbm.hsbc.com/insights/property/putian-city-of-healthcare-phenomenon|accessdate=5 May 2016|work=Week in China|publisher=HSBC|date=2014-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Baidu\u2019s \"moral dilemma\" \u2013 How a Cancer Case aroused National Attention|url=https://cnspoon.com/2016/05/02/baidu-moral/|accessdate=5 May 2016|publisher=China Spoon|date=2014-06-20}}</ref>\n\n==Tourism==\n\n[[Meizhou Island]], most famous for being the legendary birthplace of the goddess [[Mazu (goddess)|Mazu]], is located closely offshore of Putian.\nAccording to legends, Mazu in her earthly incarnation died on the seashore of Xianliang Harbor, in the coastal area of Putian, where Xianliang Mazu Temple hosts pilgrims from different Chinese provinces and from [[Taiwan]], particularly for the ceremonies commemorating the goddess' death held in October.<ref>Hsun Chang, \"Multiple Religious and National Identities: Mazu Pilgrimages across the Taiwan Strait after 1987,\" in Cheng-tian Kuo (Ed.), ''Religion and Nationalism in Chinese Societies'', Amsterdam: Amsterdam University Press, 2017, 373\u2013396 (378).</ref> Because of its hosting \"the most sacred places for Mazu believers,\" Putian is known as \"Mazu's hometown.\"<ref>Hsun Chang (2017), 378.</ref>\n\n==College and universities==\n\n*[[Putian University]]\n\n==Climate==\n\n{{Weather box|width=auto\n|metric first=y\n|single line=y \n|location = Putian (1981\u20132010)\n|Jan high C = 16.5\n|Feb high C = 17.2\n|Mar high C = 19.7\n|Apr high C = 23.3\n|May high C = 27.2\n|Jun high C = 29.7\n|Jul high C = 33.1\n|Aug high C = 32.5\n|Sep high C = 30.8\n|Oct high C = 27.0\n|Nov high C = 23.0\n|Dec high C = 18.7\n|Jan mean C = 12.5\n|Feb mean C = 13.2\n|Mar mean C = 15.2\n|Apr mean C = 19.3\n|May mean C = 23.4\n|Jun mean C = 26.2\n|Jul mean C = 28.9\n|Aug mean C = 28.6\n|Sep mean C = 27.1\n|Oct mean C = 23.4\n|Nov mean C = 19.3\n|Dec mean C = 14.8\n|year mean C = \n|Jan low C = 10.0\n|Feb low C = 10.7\n|Mar low C = 12.3\n|Apr low C = 16.4\n|May low C = 20.6\n|Jun low C = 23.6\n|Jul low C = 25.8\n|Aug low C = 25.6\n|Sep low C = 24.6\n|Oct low C = 21.1\n|Nov low C = 16.9\n|Dec low C = 12.2\n|Jan record high C = 27.0 |Jan record low C = 1.5\n|Feb record high C = 31.1 |Feb record low C = 4.1\n|Mar record high C = 30.3 |Mar record low C = 2.8\n|Apr record high C = 32.0 |Apr record low C = 9.1\n|May record high C = 33.8 |May record low C = 15.0\n|Jun record high C = 35.6 |Jun record low C = 16.2\n|Jul record high C = 36.9 |Jul record low C = 22.0\n|Aug record high C = 36.7 |Aug record low C = 21.5\n|Sep record high C = 36.4 |Sep record low C = 19.8\n|Oct record high C = 33.5 |Oct record low C = 13.2\n|Nov record high C = 31.1 |Nov record low C = 6.3\n|Dec record high C = 28.4 |Dec record low C = 1.8\n|year high C=  |year low C= \n|year high F = |year low F =\n|precipi