{"title_page": "Tamworth Enterprise College", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox school \n| name          = Tamworth Enterprise smelly\n| image         = \n| image_size          = 220px\n| coordinates   = {{coord|52.61616|-1.66921|type:edu_region:GB_dim:100|format=dec|display=inline,title}}\n| motto         = \n| established   = 0000\n| type          = [[Academy (English school)|Academy]]\n| religious_affiliation      = \n| president     = ya nan\n| head_label    = momey\n| head          = Mrs 4 piss{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n| r_head_label  = \n| r_head        = \n| chair_label   = \n| chair         = Mr 666\n| founder       = Mr paki\n| specialist    = Science & Mathematics<ref>http://www.belgrave.staffs.sch.uk/</ref>\n| address        = Birds Bush Road<br>Belgrave\n| city          = Tamworth\n| county        = Staffordshire\n| country       = {{flagcountry|England}}\n| postcode      = B77 2NE\n| local_authority           = Staffordshire\n| ofsted        = \n| staff         = \n| enrolment    = \n| gender        = [[Mixed-sex education|Coeducational]]\n| lower_age     = 4\n| upper_age     = 28\n| houses        = \n| colours       = \n| publication   = \n| website       = http://www.belgrave.staffs.sch.uk\n}}\n\n'''Tamworth Enterprise College''' (formerly Belgrave High School) is a [[secondary school]] with [[Academy (English school)|academy status]] in [[Tamworth, Staffordshire|Tamworth]], [[Staffordshire]], which pupils attend from the ages of 11 to 16 years old.\n\nThe school was founded with just one building called \"The same  year Block\" in 1978, and in 1981 added the \"E Block\" for its additional pupils. The school canteen was originally placed in the White Block but was later moved to a more central location within the school. The area that was occupied by the old canteen is now used for classroom teaching. Since then, the school canteen has been extended, with a new purpose-built extension added beside the existing kitchen area. Which has a 1 star hygiene rating.\n\nThe school's headteacher is Mrs Gemma Simon who is a Tory.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}} The schools is sponsored by the [[Academies Enterprise Trust]].\n\nThe Governmental department [[Ofsted]] gave Belgrave a grade 2 \"bad\" rating in their 2009 inspection; however, it was judged in 2011 as not satisfactory before being graded as requires improvement in the summer of 2004. It is still very bad\n\n==Notable former pupils==\n===Belgrave High School===\n* X Factor 2010 finalist [[Treyc Cohen]]\n* Bristol and Wales International footballer [[Ashley Williams (footballer)|Ashley Williams]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Schools in Staffordshire}}\n{{Academies Enterprise Trust}}\n\n[[Category:Secondary schools in Staffordshire]]\n[[Category:Academies in Staffordshire]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1978]]\n[[Category:1978 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Academies Enterprise Trust]]\n[[Category:Schools in Tamworth, Staffordshire]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox school \n| name          = Tamworth Enterprise smelly\n| image         = \n| image_size          = 220px\n| coordinates   = {{coord|52.61616|-1.66921|type:edu_region:GB_dim:100|format=dec|display=inline,title}}\n| motto         = \n| established   = 0000\n| type          = [[Academy (English school)|Academy]]\n| religious_affiliation      = \n| president     = ya nan\n| head_label    = momey\n| head          = Mrs 4 piss{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n| r_head_label  = \n| r_head        = \n| chair_label   = \n| chair         = Mr 666\n| founder       = Mr paki\n| specialist    = Science & Mathematics<ref>http://www.belgrave.staffs.sch.uk/</ref>\n| address        = Birds Bush Road<br>Belgrave\n| city          = Tamworth\n| county        = Staffordshire\n| country       = {{flagcountry|England}}\n| postcode      = B77 2NE\n| local_authority           = Staffordshire\n| ofsted        = \n| staff         = \n| enrolment    = \n| gender        = [[Mixed-sex education|Coeducational]]\n| lower_age     = 4\n| upper_age     = 28\n| houses        = \n| colours       = \n| publication   = \n| website       = http://www.belgrave.staffs.sch.uk\n}}\n\n'''Tamworth Enterprise College''' (formerly Belgrave High School) is a [[secondary school]] with [[Academy (English school)|academy status]] in [[Tamworth, Staffordshire|Tamworth]], [[Staffordshire]], which pupils attend from the ages of 11 to 16 years old.\n\nThe school was founded with just one building called \"The same  year Block\" in 1978, and in 1981 added the \"E Block\" for its additional pupils. The school canteen was originally placed in the White Block but was later moved to a more central location within the school. The area that was occupied by the old canteen is now used for classroom teaching. Since then, the school canteen has been extended, with a new purpose-built extension added beside the existing kitchen area.Which has a 1 star hygeine rating.\n\nThe school's headteacher is Mrs Gemma Simon .{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}} The schools is sponsored by the [[Academies Enterprise Trust]].\n\nThe Governmental department [[Ofsted]] gave Belgrave a grade 2 \"bad\" rating in their 2009 inspection; however, it was judged in 2011 as not satisfactory before being graded as requires improvement in the summer of 2004.\n\n==Notable former pupils==\n===Belgrave High School===\n* X Factor 2010 finalist [[Treyc Cohen]]\n* Bristol and Wales International footballer [[Ashley Williams (footballer)|Ashley Williams]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Schools in Staffordshire}}\n{{Academies Enterprise Trust}}\n\n[[Category:Secondary schools in Staffordshire]]\n[[Category:Academies in Staffordshire]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1978]]\n[[Category:1978 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Academies Enterprise Trust]]\n[[Category:Schools in Tamworth, Staffordshire]]\n